<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="30" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1556,1688]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1629,1653]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is derived from the Latin word 
<emphasis box="[815,893,1628,1652]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">clavus,</emphasis>
nail, with the suffix – 
<emphasis box="[1144,1195,1629,1652]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">gera</emphasis>
, bearing, referring to the prominent, clawlike apical tooth of the gonostylus.
</paragraph>
